      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARIS KAY (3) continued the consistent form when fourth in a higher-graded race last start at this venue. Recorded back-to-back placings prior and should have no excuses from this advantageous draw. Finds a suitable assignment and may prove tough to beat. POPPY POPSTAR (7) is in good form with top-three finishes at her last 11 starts including four wins, most recently recording a third at Ballarat. Has to contend with a very wide draw but with even luck she is capable of continuing her fine form. I AM HARRO (4) has been producing some good efforts from the back row including a win two back at this circuit and distance. Can be competitive returning to the front line. PARIS JAMILLA (6) broke last start but did well to place after working here prior and recorded back-to-back wins in May so is worth another chance.",
